        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 1:38PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 138 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northwest of Hendersonville, or near Fletcher, moving east at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hendersonville, Mills River, Fletcher, Mountain Home, Dana, Horse
Shoe, and Forge Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
